    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/32585 will recalculate the width if we pass `title` opts by using `strdisplaywidth(opts.title)` without considering that we also supports `title` as tuple of `[string,hl-group]`\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\n2. `:lua vim.lsp.util.open_floating_preview({ 'Hello' }, 'plaintext', { title = {{'Title\n', 'Normal'}} })`\n\nWill give us `E5108: Error executing lua Vim:E730: Using a List as a String` error\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-2060+g175c09bd66\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nNA\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux alp 6.12.7-0-edge #\\1-Alpine SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Fri, 27 Dec 2024 17:33:58 +0000 x86_64 Linux\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
